536
00:33:37,583 --> 00:33:40,883
The Audit Team is doing all sorts to try to gain influence.

537
00:33:41,253 --> 00:33:43,283
- I want a report. - On what?

538
00:33:43,423 --> 00:33:47,224
On the construction market for the second half of the year?

539
00:33:47,224 --> 00:33:48,954
On everything about Shin Cha Il.

540
00:33:49,323 --> 00:33:50,463
Oh, that?

541
00:33:50,494 --> 00:33:53,533
I came in early a few days ago...

542
00:33:53,533 --> 00:33:56,363
and read through his resume again.

543
00:33:56,363 --> 00:33:58,064
So I know a lot.

544
00:33:58,604 --> 00:33:59,633
He graduated from Sunghan University...

545
00:33:59,633 --> 00:34:01,874
I want to know everything that isn't on his resume.

546
00:34:02,474 --> 00:34:03,744
If there's not enough,

547
00:34:03,943 --> 00:34:06,474
a new notice of transfer will go up right next to this.

548
00:34:07,374 --> 00:34:08,443
I understand.

549
00:34:13,014 --> 00:34:16,153
It's nice to have you join us for lunch, sir.

550
00:34:17,524 --> 00:34:19,423
I hope they serve something nice today.

551
00:34:19,823 --> 00:34:21,024
What's for lunch?

552
00:34:21,624 --> 00:34:25,564
Spicy stir-fried squid, pork cutlet, and the last one is...

553
00:34:26,834 --> 00:34:28,264
It's from the Audit Team.

554
00:34:28,264 --> 00:34:30,033
Are they doing to do some real work?

555
00:34:30,104 --> 00:34:32,104
- It must be the new manager. - Yes.

556
00:34:32,104 --> 00:34:33,403
(The Audit Team will accept reports from staff.)

557
00:34:33,934 --> 00:34:36,204
Oh, dear. Work will start flooding in.

558
00:34:36,204 --> 00:34:38,503
Hey. I only gave half a vote.

559
00:34:38,974 --> 00:34:41,274
You gathered our opinions too.

560
00:34:41,343 --> 00:34:42,783
It comes with the territory.

561
00:34:43,213 --> 00:34:45,954
Let's decide who will manage the online report forum.

562
00:34:49,653 --> 00:34:50,883
You do it, Mr. Gu.

563
00:34:54,724 --> 00:34:56,394
Okay. I'll do my best.

564
00:34:57,593 --> 00:34:58,664
Good luck.

565
00:34:58,664 --> 00:34:59,834
- Squid. - Thanks.

566
00:35:15,213 --> 00:35:16,483
What brought you here?

567
00:35:18,443 --> 00:35:21,414
I'm here because I heard Gun Woong was getting better.

568
00:35:22,354 --> 00:35:23,724
I called him.

569
00:35:23,923 --> 00:35:25,084
I'm glad you did.

570
00:35:25,084 --> 00:35:26,193
How is he doing?

571
00:35:26,524 --> 00:35:27,954
He's much better.

572
00:35:28,394 --> 00:35:31,363
The doctor thinks he'll wake up soon.

573
00:35:41,073 --> 00:35:43,544
I'm sorry to say this after visiting a patient,

574
00:35:44,044 --> 00:35:45,843
but we're under-performing terribly.

575
00:35:46,573 --> 00:35:48,814
Stock prices fall more each day.

576
00:35:50,244 --> 00:35:52,014
The economic sensory index is at an all-time low...

577
00:35:52,014 --> 00:35:53,684
and the construction market's future is uncertain.

578
00:35:54,854 --> 00:35:56,724
We have to reduce the lots to parcel out.

579
00:35:57,383 --> 00:35:59,894
That's why it's hard to run a company.

580
00:36:00,624 --> 00:36:03,124
You must know how to get through the dark times.

581
00:36:03,923 --> 00:36:07,164
We'll gain an advantage in winning contracts once J-BIMS is completed.

582
00:36:07,463 --> 00:36:09,604
Okay. I look forward to seeing that.

583
00:36:10,704 --> 00:36:13,604
How are things with Dae Woong? Do you get along?

584
00:36:16,003 --> 00:36:17,774
The worst spectacle ever...

585
00:36:17,774 --> 00:36:20,173
is brothers fighting over a company.

586
00:36:21,943 --> 00:36:25,283
It would've been nice if your father had divided things before he died.

587
00:36:46,204 --> 00:36:47,274
(J-BIMS Sneak Preview)

588
00:36:50,144 --> 00:36:52,173
"Vision and innovation?"

589
00:36:53,443 --> 00:36:54,474
How nice.

590
00:36:55,474 --> 00:36:57,014
Nice gibberish.

591
00:37:00,514 --> 00:37:02,883
(J-BIMS Sneak Preview)

592
00:37:18,133 --> 00:37:19,274
Welcome.

593
00:37:23,044 --> 00:37:25,673
- I'll take a gukbap. - Okay.

594
00:37:27,213 --> 00:37:28,874
Mr. Shin! Hello.

595
00:37:29,613 --> 00:37:32,753
I don't want to eat alone. May I join you?

596
00:37:48,394 --> 00:37:50,934
Are you eating out for dinner?

597
00:37:50,934 --> 00:37:52,363
Is no one home today?

598
00:37:52,363 --> 00:37:53,803
There's no one else at home.

599
00:37:53,934 --> 00:37:55,204
You must live alone.

600
00:37:56,573 --> 00:37:57,573
Thank you.

601
00:37:57,573 --> 00:37:58,874
- Enjoy. - I will.

602
00:38:03,644 --> 00:38:04,644
Mr. Shin.

603
00:38:06,454 --> 00:38:09,383
Ever since you came, our team started to change.

604
00:38:10,783 --> 00:38:13,593
We're becoming a real audit team.

605
00:38:15,394 --> 00:38:17,193
As a member of the Audit Team,

606
00:38:17,193 --> 00:38:19,224
I feel responsible and proud.

607
00:38:20,334 --> 00:38:21,363
Also,

608
00:38:23,033 --> 00:38:25,533
my new goal is to become someone like you.

609
00:38:26,403 --> 00:38:28,274
You say I should be suspicious of everyone.

610
00:38:28,503 --> 00:38:30,474
It's still hard for me to grasp those words.

611
00:38:30,774 --> 00:38:33,943
Although you say that, I know you trust your team.

612
00:38:33,943 --> 00:38:34,974
Isn't that right?

613
00:38:37,983 --> 00:38:39,044
Please enjoy your meal.

614
00:38:43,724 --> 00:38:45,153
This looks great.

615
00:39:23,323 --> 00:39:24,923
As a member of the Audit Team,

616
00:39:24,923 --> 00:39:27,064
I feel responsible and proud.

617
00:39:27,334 --> 00:39:29,863
My new goal is to become someone like you.

618
00:39:41,544 --> 00:39:42,613
Yes, Cha Il. What is it?

619
00:39:42,613 --> 00:39:46,184
It’s the construction supply purchase audit report you worked on.

620
00:39:46,184 --> 00:39:49,253
Gosh, did you study something that was already settled?

621
00:39:50,184 --> 00:39:52,454
That's our future ace. You're so reliable.

622
00:39:55,153 --> 00:39:57,363
What is it? Is there a problem?

623
00:39:58,294 --> 00:40:01,693
I found something strange while studying the purchase list.

624
00:40:01,693 --> 00:40:04,434
Gosh. I should've explained it to you in advance.

625
00:40:05,033 --> 00:40:07,303
You're new to the job, so you must be shocked.

626
00:40:07,573 --> 00:40:11,003
Of course, the actual amount of rebar bought was 300 tons.

627
00:40:11,604 --> 00:40:12,644
Then...

628
00:40:13,374 --> 00:40:16,014
Why did we pay the company for 420 tons worth of rebar?

629
00:40:16,084 --> 00:40:19,184
Because other supplies we bought from them were included in it.

630
00:40:19,854 --> 00:40:21,684
It'd be awkward to list them one by one.

631
00:40:22,153 --> 00:40:25,454
Rebar is a major supply, so whenever we purchase them,

632
00:40:25,454 --> 00:40:26,553
we add others on top of it.

633
00:40:26,553 --> 00:40:27,693
But still...

634
00:40:28,753 --> 00:40:30,724
Shouldn't it be recorded accurately?

635
00:40:31,593 --> 00:40:33,463
Yes, you're right.

636
00:40:33,764 --> 00:40:35,164
But when you're constructing a building,

637
00:40:35,164 --> 00:40:37,233
you need a lot of extra supplies.

638
00:40:37,403 --> 00:40:40,974
But they're too petty to make a separate payment form.

639
00:40:44,144 --> 00:40:46,244
What is it? Does it look like I'm turning a blind eye...

640
00:40:46,244 --> 00:40:47,943
to people sneaking out rebars and taking bribes?

641
00:40:47,943 --> 00:40:49,544
- No, I... - Are you afraid...

642
00:40:49,544 --> 00:40:51,084
the lack of rebars will lead the building to fall?

643
00:40:51,084 --> 00:40:53,053
- I don't mean that at all. - Cha Il.

644
00:40:53,213 --> 00:40:55,253
Don't look at the small things. Look at the big picture.

645
00:40:55,713 --> 00:40:58,624
The Audit Team is about looking at the overall flow.

646
00:41:00,454 --> 00:41:01,494
Let's go back.

647
00:41:20,874 --> 00:41:22,544
- Hello. - Hello.

648
00:41:22,544 --> 00:41:23,883
- Hello. - Hello.

649
00:41:23,883 --> 00:41:24,943
Hello!

650
00:41:30,323 --> 00:41:31,423
Hello!

651
00:41:32,783 --> 00:41:33,994
- Hello. - Hello.

652
00:41:38,064 --> 00:41:40,693
- Gosh! - What are you doing?

653
00:41:40,693 --> 00:41:42,863
- My goodness. - What is he doing?

654
00:41:45,704 --> 00:41:46,774
Don't come near me!

655
00:41:46,774 --> 00:41:48,033
What's the matter?

656
00:41:48,033 --> 00:41:49,073
I said, don't come near me!

657
00:41:49,544 --> 00:41:51,144
Don't come...

658
00:41:53,144 --> 00:41:54,974
I want to report workplace bullying.

659
00:41:54,974 --> 00:41:57,383
- Be careful! - Fire.

660
00:41:57,644 --> 00:41:59,514
- Yoon Woo. - Don't come closer!

661
00:41:59,883 --> 00:42:00,914
All right.

662
00:42:01,053 --> 00:42:04,124
I won't go close. Let's turn that off and talk.

663
00:42:06,423 --> 00:42:07,624
Don't come near me!

664
00:42:13,863 --> 00:42:16,604
Are you insane? How dare you try to start a fire?

665
00:42:19,233 --> 00:42:20,303
Do you think this is a show?

666
00:42:21,073 --> 00:42:22,173
Get to work!

667
00:42:24,704 --> 00:42:25,774
Take care of this.

668
00:42:25,774 --> 00:42:27,974
Yoon Woo, are you okay?

669
00:42:32,744 --> 00:42:33,783
Yoon Woo...

670
00:42:36,431 --> 00:42:38,761
The informant is mentally unstable,

671
00:42:38,761 --> 00:42:41,170
so we should give him some time to calm down.

672
00:42:42,900 --> 00:42:46,000
Ms. Yoon, I heard you started work with Mr. Oh Yoon Woo too.

673
00:42:46,000 --> 00:42:47,011
Yes.

674
00:42:47,971 --> 00:42:49,710
During our new employee training,

675
00:42:49,710 --> 00:42:52,281
Mr. Oh was voted the most popular. He had a good personality.

676
00:42:52,881 --> 00:42:55,551
I wonder what drove him to almost set himself on fire.

677
00:42:55,551 --> 00:42:58,721
He must have suffered under his superior.

678
00:43:01,120 --> 00:43:02,120
Gosh.

679
00:43:02,120 --> 00:43:03,861
They must have tortured him.

680
00:43:04,891 --> 00:43:07,091
But is there such a person on the Technology Development Team?

681
00:43:07,690 --> 00:43:08,730
I haven't heard of anyone.

682
00:43:09,391 --> 00:43:12,031
But isn't that team extremely busy...

683
00:43:12,031 --> 00:43:13,330
with preparing for the upcoming J-BIMS demonstration?

684
00:43:13,330 --> 00:43:14,330
They are.

685
00:43:15,600 --> 00:43:16,971
(President Hwang Se Woong)

686
00:43:17,801 --> 00:43:18,900
Shin Cha Il speaking.

687
00:43:21,641 --> 00:43:22,641
Okay.

688
00:43:24,080 --> 00:43:26,381
We'll do the interview after I meet with President Hwang.

689
00:43:31,051 --> 00:43:32,850
I heard someone caused a disturbance in the lobby...

690
00:43:32,850 --> 00:43:35,150
- and that the Audit Team took him. - Yes.

691
00:43:35,391 --> 00:43:38,120
We'll investigate as soon as the informant finds his calm.

692
00:43:39,190 --> 00:43:40,830
I have a request to make regarding this case.

693
00:43:44,801 --> 00:43:46,600
(President's office)

694
00:43:56,210 --> 00:43:57,611
(Changing the future of JU Construction!)

695
00:43:57,611 --> 00:43:59,011
(J-BIMS Sneak Preview)

696
00:44:05,750 --> 00:44:08,020
I had it thoroughly researched...

697
00:44:08,020 --> 00:44:10,690
using all of my networks.

698
00:44:10,920 --> 00:44:12,020
You can trust it.

699
00:44:12,020 --> 00:44:15,031
Gosh, that Shin Cha Il is some piece of work.

700
00:44:15,161 --> 00:44:17,830
I honestly didn't think...

701
00:44:17,830 --> 00:44:19,971
it would be this bad.

702
00:44:21,370 --> 00:44:25,000
Mr. Hwang, you should go to the Audit Team and expose him.

703
00:44:25,270 --> 00:44:27,971
He'd be humiliated in front of his subordinates.

704
00:44:27,971 --> 00:44:30,011
He might even decide to leave voluntarily.

705
00:44:30,841 --> 00:44:31,841
Yes.

706
00:44:32,411 --> 00:44:34,281
It's no fun to release it at once.

707
00:44:36,111 --> 00:44:37,480
I'll make him wither away.

708
00:44:38,350 --> 00:44:39,650
Slowly.

709
00:44:44,920 --> 00:44:45,920
Yoon Woo.

710
00:44:46,830 --> 00:44:48,861
Just tell me everything that happened...

711
00:44:49,091 --> 00:44:50,531
as much as you can remember.

712
00:44:53,900 --> 00:44:55,600
You look gaunt.

713
00:44:57,400 --> 00:44:58,770
It breaks my heart.

714
00:44:59,701 --> 00:45:02,540
You were so happy to be assigned to the Technology Development Team.

715
00:45:03,310 --> 00:45:04,341
I was.

716
00:45:06,980 --> 00:45:08,710
It was the team I wanted.

717
00:45:12,850 --> 00:45:16,020
The Audit Team will help you as much as we can.

718
00:45:16,891 --> 00:45:19,931
Don't worry and tell us everything.

719
00:45:25,830 --> 00:45:28,000
Do you mean you were constantly bullied...

720
00:45:28,100 --> 00:45:30,801
by Technology Development Team's Junior Manager Park Jae Wan?

721
00:45:31,801 --> 00:45:34,540
Do you remember when the bullying began?

722
00:45:40,911 --> 00:45:42,710
I don't know exactly,

723
00:45:43,250 --> 00:45:45,150
but I think it has been three to four months.

724
00:45:47,721 --> 00:45:49,420
Why did you put up with it...

725
00:45:49,850 --> 00:45:51,991
for that long only to speak up now?

726
00:45:53,460 --> 00:45:56,431
I'd wanted to join the Technology Development Team since I started.

727
00:45:56,830 --> 00:45:58,900
Although I was sent to another team at first,

728
00:45:59,201 --> 00:46:01,201
I worked and tried hard to transfer.

729
00:46:02,600 --> 00:46:03,701
More than anything,

730
00:46:04,341 --> 00:46:05,971
I was proud to be part of...

731
00:46:06,301 --> 00:46:09,210
the J-BIMS project that held the company's future.

732
00:46:11,310 --> 00:46:13,451
So I put up with it though it was hard.

733
00:46:14,710 --> 00:46:16,551
- Goodness. - Hello.

734
00:46:16,580 --> 00:46:18,020
- Hello. - Hello.

735
00:46:18,551 --> 00:46:19,551
Hello.

736
00:46:26,261 --> 00:46:28,460
(Employee Number, Password)

737
00:46:30,261 --> 00:46:31,460
(Access denied)

738
00:46:35,571 --> 00:46:36,571
(Access denied)

739
00:46:36,571 --> 00:46:39,571
Mr. Park, there's an error in the access system.

740
00:46:39,571 --> 00:46:41,210
It's not an error.

741
00:46:41,511 --> 00:46:43,641
- What? - You no longer...

742
00:46:43,710 --> 00:46:46,040
have access to the J-BIMS development folder.

743
00:46:46,141 --> 00:46:47,650
Your access was revoked.

744
00:46:47,850 --> 00:46:49,511
I got approval already.

745
00:46:53,750 --> 00:46:56,960
Does that mean I can no longer help develop J-BIMS?

746
00:46:57,161 --> 00:47:00,491
That's right. You're off the project now.

747
00:47:00,861 --> 00:47:02,761
There are other things to do.

748
00:47:03,161 --> 00:47:05,761
Oh, right. Security needed something.

749
00:47:07,330 --> 00:47:08,471
Do stuff like this.

750
00:47:08,670 --> 00:47:10,841
The others are busy with the J-BIMS preview.

751
00:47:12,670 --> 00:47:13,710
Are you done?

752
00:47:14,111 --> 00:47:15,511
- Almost. - Okay.

753
00:47:24,181 --> 00:47:25,620
(Access denied)

754
00:47:25,620 --> 00:47:26,850
I could take anything else...

755
00:47:27,020 --> 00:47:29,750
but not being excluded from the J-BIMS project.

756
00:47:30,321 --> 00:47:31,361
That...

757
00:47:32,060 --> 00:47:34,190
practically means they want me gone.

758
00:47:37,201 --> 00:47:38,730
It must've been rough, Yoon Woo.

759
00:47:48,540 --> 00:47:50,310
I must grasp the situation.

760
00:47:50,411 --> 00:47:53,580
You can carry out the next interview.

761
00:47:55,350 --> 00:47:56,920
- Me? - The more you do it,

762
00:47:56,920 --> 00:47:58,120
the more you learn.

763
00:47:58,781 --> 00:48:01,790
Draw them into the conversation and get as many details as you can.

764
00:48:03,150 --> 00:48:04,391
With a steely gaze.

765
00:48:13,531 --> 00:48:15,071
(Do not film, Do not take off)

766
00:48:15,531 --> 00:48:16,940
- You can enter now. - Okay.

767
00:48:16,940 --> 00:48:20,770
(Use of phones prohibited, security cameras are recording)

768
00:48:26,381 --> 00:48:29,781
(JU Construction)

769
00:48:29,850 --> 00:48:35,020
(Manager's Office)

770
00:48:35,190 --> 00:48:36,190
Come in.

771
00:48:43,600 --> 00:48:44,801
Sorry.

772
00:48:45,131 --> 00:48:47,801
I'm terrible at cleaning up.

773
00:48:48,600 --> 00:48:49,670
Please sit.

774
00:48:56,670 --> 00:48:58,940
You got here really fast.

775
00:48:59,181 --> 00:49:01,381
I only just got the call that you'd be coming.

776
00:49:01,451 --> 00:49:03,850
It's a simple interview. I thought we should get it over with.

777
00:49:04,420 --> 00:49:05,420
I see.

778
00:49:06,281 --> 00:49:09,520
I can't spare you much time.

779
00:49:09,750 --> 00:49:11,161
I hope you understand.

780
00:49:13,221 --> 00:49:15,261
- May I use this? - Just a moment.

781
00:49:21,230 --> 00:49:23,330
That's crumpled up. Here's a new sheet.

782
00:49:28,210 --> 00:49:29,511
I'll begin, then.

783
00:49:30,281 --> 00:49:32,710
Employee Oh Yoon Woo reported Junior Manager Park Jae Wan...

784
00:49:32,710 --> 00:49:34,350
for workplace bullying.

785
00:49:37,250 --> 00:49:38,520
It's my fault.

786
00:49:39,181 --> 00:49:40,290
Trying to set himself on fire?

787
00:49:41,451 --> 00:49:44,361
I had no idea Yoon Woo was suffering,

788
00:49:45,261 --> 00:49:46,361
and I feel guilty.

789
00:49:46,830 --> 00:49:49,161
I heard they were working on the same thing.

790
00:49:49,361 --> 00:49:51,560
Yes. They were developing a cost-optimizing engine.

791
00:49:52,031 --> 00:49:53,431
Mr. Park headed the project,

792
00:49:53,431 --> 00:49:55,201
and Yoon Woo was assisting.

793
00:49:55,330 --> 00:49:58,040
Mr. Oh said he was verbally abused.

794
00:49:58,600 --> 00:50:00,310
What do you say about that?

795
00:50:08,451 --> 00:50:11,051
Mr. Park is quite sensitive.

796
00:50:11,381 --> 00:50:13,591
He has an important role which means a lot of work.

797
00:50:14,120 --> 00:50:15,620
Yoon Woo was assisting him,

798
00:50:15,620 --> 00:50:18,391
but he made lots of small mistakes and didn't know much about math.

799
00:50:19,861 --> 00:50:22,531
Mr. Park did nag a lot and got annoyed often,

800
00:50:22,531 --> 00:50:23,600
but...

801
00:50:24,830 --> 00:50:26,431
calling that verbal abuse...

802
00:50:26,460 --> 00:50:30,301
Why did you exclude Mr. Oh from the J-BIMS project?

803
00:50:30,600 --> 00:50:31,971
It was Mr. Park's suggestion.

804
00:50:32,641 --> 00:50:34,710
He said Yoon Woo was more of a hindrance than help.

805
00:50:36,471 --> 00:50:38,040
I do feel sorry for Yoon Woo,

806
00:50:38,781 --> 00:50:40,250
but work is more important.

807
00:50:55,491 --> 00:50:57,060
I'm Audit Team Manager Shin Cha Il.

808
00:50:57,330 --> 00:50:59,730
I would like to conduct an interview.

809
00:51:19,681 --> 00:51:21,491
- Hello. - Hello.

810
00:51:21,790 --> 00:51:23,221
I'm Yoon Seo Jin from the Audit Team.

811
00:51:23,420 --> 00:51:24,761
I'd like to interview you.

812
00:51:44,080 --> 00:51:45,881
- That's Mr. Park, right? - Yes.

813
00:51:46,040 --> 00:51:47,511
Why does he look so haggard?

814
00:51:47,810 --> 00:51:49,710
You'd think he was being bullied.

815
00:51:49,951 --> 00:51:51,350
He's as thin as a stick.

816
00:51:51,750 --> 00:51:52,850
He is.

817
00:51:53,420 --> 00:51:54,920
(Yes! Chicken)

818
00:51:54,920 --> 00:51:57,020
Yoon Woo, it's been so long.

819
00:51:57,460 --> 00:51:59,161
You should've come over more often.

820
00:51:59,161 --> 00:52:00,161
Yes.

821
00:52:00,330 --> 00:52:01,931
Dad! When will the chicken be ready?

822
00:52:01,931 --> 00:52:03,491
Right now.

823
00:52:03,491 --> 00:52:04,830
Here it comes.

824
00:52:05,500 --> 00:52:06,830
There.

825
00:52:08,701 --> 00:52:11,641
Yoon Woo, you said we served the best chicken.

826
00:52:11,770 --> 00:52:12,900
Why haven't you been by?

827
00:52:13,341 --> 00:52:14,641
Did you find another place?

828
00:52:14,641 --> 00:52:15,710
Yes.

829
00:52:16,940 --> 00:52:19,540
Something came up.

830
00:52:19,841 --> 00:52:20,911
Like what?

831
00:52:21,710 --> 00:52:22,781
You punk.

832
00:52:22,781 --> 00:52:25,020
If something had come up, you should've come to me.

833
00:52:25,120 --> 00:52:26,850
We could've talked over a beer.

834
00:52:27,620 --> 00:52:30,221
- Enjoy the food. - Yes, eat.

835
00:52:31,790 --> 00:52:33,730
Yoon Woo, eat this first.

836
00:52:35,230 --> 00:52:36,631
What do you eat when you feel down?

837
00:52:36,830 --> 00:52:38,031
Fried chicken.

838
00:52:38,361 --> 00:52:40,301
Our drumsticks are amazing.

839
00:52:40,370 --> 00:52:41,370
Come on, eat.

840
00:52:45,571 --> 00:52:47,141
Isn't it good?

841
00:52:47,210 --> 00:52:48,571
The stress melts away, right?

842
00:52:48,841 --> 00:52:50,611
Hey, how about a beer?

843
00:52:53,411 --> 00:52:56,480
Yoon Woo. Mr. Shin gave you time off, so rest.

844
00:52:56,480 --> 00:52:58,150
Let's not think about work...

845
00:52:58,150 --> 00:53:00,120
and dig into some chicken.

846
00:53:03,591 --> 00:53:05,861
Okay. I'll... My gosh.

847
00:53:05,920 --> 00:53:07,960
I'll give you the other drumstick too.

848
00:53:08,131 --> 00:53:10,661
Do you know what this means? I'm letting you eat both.

849
00:53:12,131 --> 00:53:14,931
You must eat to be strong, right?

850
00:53:15,770 --> 00:53:17,000
You look so nice when you smile.

851
00:53:17,000 --> 00:53:18,801
Dad! Where's the beer?

852
00:53:20,000 --> 00:53:22,810
Mr. Oh and Mr. Park gave conflicting statements.

853
00:53:23,341 --> 00:53:26,440
Why do you think Mr. Park bullied you?

854
00:53:26,710 --> 00:53:28,710
Does he treat his other teammates the same way?

855
00:53:28,850 --> 00:53:30,551
I do lack some skills,

856
00:53:30,750 --> 00:53:32,850
but he speaks to me in an extra nasty manner.

857
00:53:33,520 --> 00:53:35,391
You still haven't solved the error?

858
00:53:35,891 --> 00:53:37,761
This will delay the other parts too.

859
00:53:37,761 --> 00:53:40,631
I'm sorry, sir. I'll finish that within the week.

860
00:53:41,261 --> 00:53:42,460
Please do that.

861
00:53:42,460 --> 00:53:43,801
Let's end the meeting.

862
00:53:44,161 --> 00:53:45,730
- Thanks. - Thank you.

863
00:53:48,000 --> 00:53:49,670
Mr. Oh. Can I have a word?

864
00:53:51,841 --> 00:53:53,770
How many times must I tell you?

865
00:53:53,770 --> 00:53:55,370
What's this for?

866
00:53:55,540 --> 00:53:58,841
Why do you need a head when you don't use it to think?

867
00:54:02,580 --> 00:54:05,120
You pointed out his shortcomings,

868
00:54:05,150 --> 00:54:06,721
but you weren't verbally abusive?

869
00:54:06,850 --> 00:54:08,420
Yes, that's right.

870
00:54:11,721 --> 00:54:15,131
We're fixing just one thing, and you're making me repeat myself.

871
00:54:15,761 --> 00:54:16,991
How many times must I tell you?

872
00:54:17,500 --> 00:54:18,531
I apologize.

873
00:54:18,730 --> 00:54:20,830
Others are suffering because we're slow.

874
00:54:21,000 --> 00:54:24,071
I need you to think a bit more when you work.

875
00:54:26,801 --> 00:54:30,011
Is there a witness or evidence of the verbal abuse?

876
00:54:30,071 --> 00:54:31,540
Of course there isn't.

877
00:54:31,580 --> 00:54:33,850
I never bullied or verbally abused anyone.

878
00:54:33,980 --> 00:54:34,980
(Mr. Park, here's the revised file.)

879
00:54:34,980 --> 00:54:37,451
(File error: File is damaged or not compatible.)

880
00:54:39,821 --> 00:54:41,350
I apologize.

881
00:54:41,520 --> 00:54:44,190
I can't run the simulation right now.

882
00:54:44,190 --> 00:54:45,690
I'll get a new file...

883
00:54:46,620 --> 00:54:47,631
and show it to you.

884
00:54:47,631 --> 00:54:50,361
Is this how you prepare for a meeting?

885
00:54:50,701 --> 00:54:52,230
I'm really sorry.

886
00:54:55,071 --> 00:54:56,100
Mr. Oh.

887
00:54:56,670 --> 00:54:58,500
How could you mess up the attached file?

888
00:54:58,500 --> 00:54:59,801
I was humiliated.

889
00:55:00,100 --> 00:55:02,940
Are you doing this on purpose because you have a grudge?

890
00:55:04,210 --> 00:55:06,241
I'd rather you speak up honestly.

891
00:55:06,980 --> 00:55:08,681
It's really stressing me out.

892
00:55:09,150 --> 00:55:12,020
It's usually when we're alone or on the phone.

893
00:55:12,480 --> 00:55:14,850
We all have a security app on our phones,

894
00:55:14,850 --> 00:55:16,190
so we can't record calls.

895
00:55:19,161 --> 00:55:21,230
- Hello, Mr. Park... - Have you lost your mind?

896
00:55:23,230 --> 00:55:26,801
What kind of idiot can't even send an email right?

897
00:55:26,931 --> 00:55:28,531
Are you doing this on purpose?

898
00:55:28,701 --> 00:55:30,230
To mess with me, right?

899
00:55:30,230 --> 00:55:31,440
No, it's not...

900
00:55:31,440 --> 00:55:33,170
You're a dimwit during work,

901
00:55:33,170 --> 00:55:35,911
but you get all smart when screwing me over.

902
00:55:36,210 --> 00:55:37,741
You wicked son of a gun.

903
00:55:37,911 --> 00:55:40,310
You're nothing but a useless piece of trash.

904
00:55:40,681 --> 00:55:41,911
Darn it!

905
00:55:55,661 --> 00:55:57,931
Even if I had shortcomings,

906
00:55:58,830 --> 00:56:01,471
getting excluded from J-BIMS was unfair.

907
00:56:01,471 --> 00:56:03,330
With the demonstration just around the corner,

908
00:56:03,330 --> 00:56:04,540
we have tons to do within a short time.

909
00:56:05,100 --> 00:56:06,741
He's not being helpful.

910
00:56:09,170 --> 00:56:10,270
Honestly,

911
00:56:10,580 --> 00:56:13,040
I want Mr. Oh Yoon Woo to leave our team.

912
00:56:13,951 --> 00:56:15,111
It's for everyone's sake.

913
00:56:18,281 --> 00:56:19,381
I'm back.

914
00:56:20,790 --> 00:56:23,051
What did the other Technology Development Team members say?

915
00:56:23,850 --> 00:56:26,060
Well... You see...

916
00:56:29,730 --> 00:56:30,960
He gets scolded a lot.

917
00:56:31,301 --> 00:56:33,701
He can't really handle his work.

918
00:56:34,301 --> 00:56:37,370
But Mr. Lee is too kind to say anything bad to him.

919
00:56:38,471 --> 00:56:39,841
If he had a temper, gosh...

920
00:56:40,440 --> 00:56:42,241
Mr. Park gets irritated easily.

921
00:56:42,440 --> 00:56:44,480
It's getting worse. He wasn't like that before.

922
00:56:45,881 --> 00:56:48,281
Mr. Oh Yoon Woo frequently makes mistakes.

923
00:56:48,350 --> 00:56:50,920
But I heard he did well under Junior Manager Shim.

924
00:56:50,980 --> 00:56:53,721
Mr. Park has Mr. Oh on a short leash.

925
00:56:53,721 --> 00:56:57,290
But he blames Mr. Oh for any delays or problems.

926
00:56:57,891 --> 00:56:59,460
We don't question about it.

927
00:56:59,591 --> 00:57:00,861
By any chance,

928
00:57:00,861 --> 00:57:03,391
did Mr. Park make an insulting remark...

929
00:57:03,391 --> 00:57:05,801
or mention Mr. Oh's family background?

930
00:57:05,830 --> 00:57:08,400
What? About Mr. Oh being an orphan?

931
00:57:09,100 --> 00:57:11,701
Gosh. That would be crossing the line.

932
00:57:11,701 --> 00:57:14,341
Mr. Park can be extremely on edge.

933
00:57:15,411 --> 00:57:16,810
But he's not that bad of a person.

934
00:57:16,911 --> 00:57:19,781
Everyone may be too busy to be concerned about others.

935
00:57:20,281 --> 00:57:22,281
But if Mr. Park had done any of those,

936
00:57:22,281 --> 00:57:23,710
we would've stepped in.

937
00:57:25,681 --> 00:57:27,991
Then Yoon Woo is making up stories.

938
00:57:29,051 --> 00:57:30,190
Nothing is clear.

939
00:57:30,661 --> 00:57:31,821
There isn't any evidence, either.

940
00:57:35,960 --> 00:57:37,900
(JU Construction)

941
00:57:39,000 --> 00:57:40,460
(Manager Lee Ji Hoon)

942
00:57:49,071 --> 00:57:50,210
Yes, Mr. Lee?

943
00:57:51,281 --> 00:57:52,611
Come inside.

944
00:57:52,841 --> 00:57:54,080
You haven't visited in a while, right, Yoon Woo?

945
00:57:54,080 --> 00:57:55,111
Hold on.

946
00:57:55,181 --> 00:57:56,281
It's okay.

947
00:57:56,281 --> 00:57:57,620
I can sleep at my house.

948
00:57:57,620 --> 00:57:59,451
Come on. Aren't we coworkers?

949
00:58:00,051 --> 00:58:01,790
Rest well at my place until tomorrow.

950
00:58:02,020 --> 00:58:03,650
I'll wrap things up at work quickly.

951
00:58:03,650 --> 00:58:04,821
Let's grab some delicious dinner.

952
00:58:10,060 --> 00:58:11,261
By the way,

953
00:58:11,531 --> 00:58:13,431
do your team members not know that...

954
00:58:13,661 --> 00:58:15,230
Mr. Park is harassing you?

955
00:58:15,500 --> 00:58:17,230
All they know is that I often get scolded.

956
00:58:18,141 --> 00:58:20,940
Mr. Park verbally abuses me only when we're alone.

957
00:58:21,870 --> 00:58:23,170
What about Mr. Lee?

958
00:58:23,471 --> 00:58:24,940
Does he get angry at you too?

959
00:58:25,241 --> 00:58:26,381
No.

960
00:58:26,580 --> 00:58:28,281
Mr. Lee is a great person.

961
00:58:32,120 --> 00:58:33,650
(JU Technology Development Team Manager Lee Ji Hoon)

962
00:58:34,491 --> 00:58:35,920
Yes, Mr. Lee?

963
00:58:35,920 --> 00:58:37,861
Mr. Oh. How are you feeling?

964
00:58:37,861 --> 00:58:39,591
I'm all right.

965
00:58:39,891 --> 00:58:41,891
(Technology Development Team Manager Lee Ji Hoon)

966
00:58:41,931 --> 00:58:45,131
I'll give you a ten-day special vacation. Get some good rest.

967
00:58:45,330 --> 00:58:47,000
Let's talk again after that.

968
00:58:47,431 --> 00:58:48,571
Mr. Lee.

969
00:58:49,031 --> 00:58:51,341
If it's ten days later, the demonstration will have ended.

970
00:58:52,770 --> 00:58:55,411
Does that mean I'm excluded from J-BIMS' completion?

971
00:58:55,641 --> 00:58:58,641
With the current situation, you can't get involved in J-BIMS.

972
00:58:59,281 --> 00:59:01,210
There isn't much time to settle...

973
00:59:01,650 --> 00:59:03,011
our emotions right now.

974
00:59:03,111 --> 00:59:06,350
No. I'll go to the office right now.

975
00:59:09,721 --> 00:59:10,920
What?

976
00:59:12,861 --> 00:59:13,991
Yes.

977
00:59:16,261 --> 00:59:17,400
Understood.

978
00:59:20,201 --> 00:59:22,071
Can you not return to working on J-BIMS?

979
00:59:22,131 --> 00:59:23,370
Mr. Lee said it was a vacation.

980
00:59:25,571 --> 00:59:27,170
But he meant I should leave the project.

981
00:59:27,841 --> 00:59:30,511
Listen, Yoon Woo. I'll go and let the Audit Team know.

982
00:59:45,391 --> 00:59:46,591
Mr. Shin.

983
00:59:46,591 --> 00:59:48,861
Giving Yoon Woo a vacation,

984
00:59:48,861 --> 00:59:50,861
Mr. Lee told him to sit out of J-BIMS.

985
00:59:52,000 --> 00:59:53,431
It's been decided that Mr. Oh's report...

986
00:59:53,431 --> 00:59:56,270
will be processed after the J-BIMS demonstration.

987
00:59:56,870 --> 00:59:58,940
Then nothing will change for Yoon Woo.

988
00:59:59,370 --> 01:00:00,670
We must investigate further.

989
01:00:02,770 --> 01:00:05,810
There is no evidence proving his allegations of verbal abuse.

990
01:00:06,210 --> 01:00:07,210
He couldn't record anything...

991
01:00:07,210 --> 01:00:09,611
due to the nature of the Technology Development Team.

992
01:00:09,611 --> 01:00:11,381
The Technology Development Team members...

993
01:00:11,381 --> 01:00:15,120
testified they had never witnessed Mr. Park verbally abuse Mr. Oh.

994
01:00:15,891 --> 01:00:17,221
Mr. Oh's report...

995
01:00:17,221 --> 01:00:19,060
is a one-sided argument at the moment.

996
01:00:19,690 --> 01:00:21,591
Considering the realistic situation,

997
01:00:21,591 --> 01:00:25,861
we will separate Mr. Park and Mr. Oh until the demonstration.

998
01:00:26,201 --> 01:00:27,870
Mr. Oh will either be put back on the team...

999
01:00:27,870 --> 01:00:30,201
or transferred to another team after the demonstration.

1000
01:00:31,241 --> 01:00:32,741
I'll go and let the Audit Team know.

1001
01:00:33,940 --> 01:00:35,911
President Hwang ordered Mr. Shin...

1002
01:00:36,111 --> 01:00:37,940
not to make a big deal out of it.

1003
01:00:39,111 --> 01:00:40,241
Is it...

1004
01:00:41,051 --> 01:00:42,281
because of President Hwang?

1005
01:00:46,980 --> 01:00:49,051
I heard he told you to close this case.

1006
01:00:51,221 --> 01:00:53,020
Is this the Audit Team...

1007
01:00:53,690 --> 01:00:55,861
suspecting everything you mentioned?

1008
01:00:57,261 --> 01:00:58,801
Yoon Woo must've felt so wronged...

1009
01:00:58,801 --> 01:01:01,201
and distressed to have wanted to burn himself to death.

1010
01:01:02,531 --> 01:01:05,741
I know that the demonstration is an important big event. I do.

1011
01:01:06,370 --> 01:01:09,370
But I don't think it's important enough to disregard one's pain.

1012
01:01:09,370 --> 01:01:10,980
We're not disregarding it.

1013
01:01:11,040 --> 01:01:12,580
The conclusion of the investigation...

1014
01:01:12,580 --> 01:01:14,350
has been postponed until ten days later.

1015
01:01:14,980 --> 01:01:16,580
Why must the victim sit out?

1016
01:01:17,210 --> 01:01:20,781
Yoon Woo did his best for the past year on J-BIMS.

1017
01:01:23,091 --> 01:01:24,460
If it benefits the company,

1018
01:01:25,290 --> 01:01:27,531
do we overlook the matter regardless of how bad it is?

1019
01:01:27,531 --> 01:01:29,931
Your personal feelings toward the informant...

1020
01:01:29,931 --> 01:01:32,631
have made you lose judgment and become biased.

1021
01:01:34,330 --> 01:01:35,370
Is that so?

1022
01:01:36,270 --> 01:01:38,000
Then what about this, Mr. Shin?

1023
01:01:39,000 --> 01:01:41,870
What if someone is going to leak the company's important technology?

1024
01:01:47,011 --> 01:01:48,181
What are you saying?

1025
01:01:48,181 --> 01:01:50,781
You may cover up the pain of a bullied individual.

1026
01:01:51,750 --> 01:01:52,951
But you will investigate...

1027
01:01:54,650 --> 01:01:55,850
a major case like this, right?

1028
01:02:04,560 --> 01:02:07,571
(The Auditors)

1029
01:02:07,571 --> 01:02:08,770
(Special thanks to Jung Dong Hwan,)

1030
01:02:08,770 --> 01:02:10,000
(Cho Han Cheul, Shin Jae Ha, Lee Joong Ok, Woo Ji Hyun.)

1031
01:02:27,591 --> 01:02:31,261
This is where leaked information is traded illegally.

1032
01:02:31,491 --> 01:02:32,591
Don't tell me...

1033
01:02:32,591 --> 01:02:33,721
J-BIMS.

1034
01:02:33,790 --> 01:02:36,190
What we need is evidence.

1035
01:02:36,631 --> 01:02:39,100
Treating people's lives like it's nothing...

1036
01:02:39,330 --> 01:02:41,701
while criticizing corruption and all.

1037
01:02:42,270 --> 01:02:44,341
It must be sickening, no?

1038
01:02:45,701 --> 01:02:47,100
Answer wisely.

1039
01:02:47,100 --> 01:02:50,141
If not, reporting to the police will be decided...

1040
01:02:50,141 --> 01:02:51,241
as soon as this investigation is over.

1041
01:02:51,381 --> 01:02:53,411
The demonstration must sail smoothly.

1042
01:02:53,681 --> 01:02:55,850
Circumstantial evidence...

1043
01:02:56,181 --> 01:02:58,451
of leaking J-BIMS key technology has been found.
